NeuroSearch Cuts 165 Positions, Expects Deeper Loss

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   W i e n b e r g
-- 
2011-09-27T08:54:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/neurosearch-cuts-165-positions-expects-deeper-loss-correct-.html
(Corrects number of jobs in headline, first paragraph.)  -- NeuroSearch A/S said it will cut
about 165 jobs over two years to reduce fixed and employee-
related costs to about 50 million kroner per year from currently
about 200 million kroner.  The company also said it will record a 2011 operating loss
on continuing operations of 370 million kroner compared with a
previous forecast of an operating loss of 300 million kroner.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christian Wienberg at 
 cwienberg@bloomberg.net  